# z Skill — Handoff Entrypoint: epic-update

This session was started via `CONTINUE_SESSION` with `forceWorkflow="z-epic-update"`.
The host has **already** validated the `<z-handoff type="work-complete">`
sentinel at the top of this prompt and parsed its typed metadata into
`session.handoffContext` (issue #695).

## Your task — enter `local:z` phase 5.E as the **orchestrator**, not the bookkeeper

`local:z` is a controller. Phase 5.E does not perform GitHub mutations directly —
it dispatches an epic-update subagent and (for epic close) an explicit user
question, per `src/local/skills/z/SKILL.md` §Phase 5.E and the manual-close
policy in `src/local/skills/using-epic-tasks/reference/github.md` §3.

1. Treat the `<z-handoff type="work-complete">` block in this prompt body as
   the session SSOT. The host verified its structure — you do not re-parse.
2. **Skip `local:z` phases 0–4** — the implementation session already shipped
   the PR. Your only job is to reflect that completion back into the parent
   epic, by orchestrating subagents.
3. **Dispatch an epic-update subagent** (`Agent`, `general-purpose`,
   `run_in_background: true`) with the following inputs:
   - Parent epic URL.
   - Block's `## Completed Subissue` URL + `## PR` URL + merge SHA (read merge
     SHA from `gh pr view --json mergeCommit` if not already in the block).
   - Block's `## Summary` (1–3 lines, behavior-level — `using-ha-thinking`
     discipline; do not embed file paths or function names).
   - Block's `## Remaining Epic Checklist`.
   - Procedure: post the Summary as a comment on the epic; flip the relevant
     line in the epic body checklist from `[ ]` to `[x]`; **do not close the
     epic** (manual-close policy below).
   - Final report: which lines were flipped, any open sub-issues, the Done-gate
     evaluation result (open sub-issues == 0 and checklist fully `[x]`?).
4. When the subagent's report returns:
   - **Done gate fails** (open sub-issues remain or checklist still has `[ ]`):
     print the remaining sub-issue list (title + URL) to the user and stop.
     Do **not** auto-chain to the next sub-issue's Handoff #1
     (using-z §Protocol Rules #3 — no auto-chain, hop budget exhausted).
   - **Done gate passes** (every sub-issue closed and checklist fully `[x]`):
     `local:UIAskUserQuestion` asking the user whether to close the epic.
     Manual close is the policy: epics close only after human Done-Done
     verification (`using-epic-tasks/reference/github.md` §3 +
     `using-epic-tasks/SKILL.md` Invariant 4). On user approval, dispatch a
     close subagent that runs the epic-close API call. On user decline or
     no-response: leave the epic open and end.

## Forbidden

- **Direct execution.** No `gh issue comment`, `gh issue edit`, `gh issue close`
  in this session. All GitHub mutations go through subagents. No `Edit` /
  `Write` against repo source files. No direct `mcp__llm__chat`. Read-only
  state probes (`gh issue view --json`, `gh api -X GET`) are allowed per
  `z/SKILL.md` §Hard Rules.
- Re-examining the epic spec or redesigning scope — that was settled when the
  epic was created.
- Marking an incomplete sub-issue as done.
- **Auto-closing the epic** based on the Done gate alone. The Done gate is
  necessary but not sufficient — explicit user approval is required per the
  manual-close policy. Auto-closing violates `using-epic-tasks` Invariant 4.
- Re-emitting `local:es` (the work session already fired it during phase 5.3).
- Automatically chaining into the next sub-issue's Handoff #1. The user must
  manually kick off the next sub-issue with `$z <subissue-url>`.

> Hop-budget enforcement (per-session limit of 1 auto-handoff) is host-side
> issue #697 — this prompt only guides the default, non-chained behavior.
